<subSubSection id="C3616553FF9DAF33D18ADEDBFB0312AA" pageId="41" pageNumber="42" type="etymology">
<paragraph id="8BC436D8FF9DAF33D18ADEDBFB0312AA" blockId="41.[151,1436,151,777]" pageId="41" pageNumber="42">
<emphasis id="B90FEACAFF9DAF33D18ADEDBFEF11291" bold="true" box="[198,343,431,457]" pageId="41" pageNumber="42">Etymology:</emphasis>
The name is after Padre Francisco Silvério Pereira, CMF (1912–1992), Brazilian scarabeidologist who described the single species here included in this genus. Gender neutral.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C3616553FF9DAF33D18ADE8BFC69111A" pageId="41" pageNumber="42" type="distribution">
