<subSubSection id="C3616553FF9DAF33D18ADD3BFD4A11BA" pageId="41" pageNumber="42" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="8BC436D8FF9DAF33D18ADD3BFA3A11E1" blockId="41.[151,1436,151,777]" pageId="41" pageNumber="42">
<emphasis id="B90FEACAFF9DAF33D18ADD3BFEE71131" bold="true" box="[198,321,591,617]" pageId="41" pageNumber="42">Remarks:</emphasis>
The main apomorphies of this genus are the presence of horns in males and two frontal concavities in females, an anterior pronotal bead, and convex discal interstriae. It may be diagnosed also by the absence of the synapomorphies supporting 
<taxonomicName id="4C7B4D5BFF9DAF33D3C3DDD4FCBD11E1" authorityName="Vaz-De-Mello" authorityYear="2008" box="[655,795,672,697]" class="Insecta" family="Scarabaeidae" genus="Onoreidium" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="41" pageNumber="42" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B90FEACAFF9DAF33D3C3DDD4FCBD11E1" box="[655,795,672,697]" italics="true" pageId="41" pageNumber="42">Onoreidium</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, its sister-genus. See more remarks under 
<emphasis id="B90FEACAFF9DAF33D444DDD4FA3A11E1" box="[1288,1436,672,697]" italics="true" pageId="41" pageNumber="42">
<taxonomicName id="4C7B4D5BFF9DAF33D444DDD4FA3E11E1" authorityName="Vaz-De-Mello" authorityYear="2008" box="[1288,1432,672,697]" class="Insecta" family="Scarabaeidae" genus="Onoreidium" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="41" pageNumber="42" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">Onoreidium</taxonomicName>
.
</emphasis>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BC436D8FF9DAF33D18ADDB3FD4A11BA" blockId="41.[151,1436,151,777]" box="[198,748,711,738]" pageId="41" pageNumber="42">
<emphasis id="B90FEACAFF9DAF33D18ADDB3FEC911B9" bold="true" box="[198,367,711,737]" pageId="41" pageNumber="42">Composition:</emphasis>
Only the 
<typeStatus id="54C0887AFF9DAF33D0A8DDBCFDB011BA" box="[484,534,712,738]" pageId="41" pageNumber="42">type</typeStatus>
species is known.
</paragraph>
